fields.name: Chicken curry
fields.description: This creamy Indian chicken curry has an unbeatable combination of flavors thanks to an array of aromatic warm spices, plain yogurt, and coconut milk.

fields.name: Lasagna
fields.ingredients: Pasta, marinara sauce, ricotta cheese, ground beef
fields.description: This classic homemade lasagna features an easy meat sauce layered with noodles and plenty of cheese.

fields.name: Baked potato
fields.description: This simple but filling dish makes an excellent, easy side.

fields.name: Spaghetti
fields.description: This classic meal is one-pot: makes it easy on the cleaning!

fields.name: Taco Bowl
fields.ingredients: Ground beef, rice, bell pepper, corn, beans
fields.description: This deconstructed taco makes it easier to size portions.

fields.name: Stir Fry
fields.description: This easy Chicken Stir Fry recipe is loaded with fresh veggies and the most delicious sauce made with honey, soy sauce, and toasted sesame oil!

fields.name: Pan chicken
fields.description: This chicken breast skillet recipe is fast, easy, and delicious. You can easily monitor the internal temperature of the meat when pan-roasting chicken. Leaving the skin on adds a lot of flavor and much-needed moisture.

fields.name: S'more
fields.description: This camping delight can even be made in the microwave!

fields.name: Cheesy Broccoli Soup
fields.description: This vegetarian dish remains filling and a crowd-pleaser.

fields.name: Quinoa Pilaf
fields.description: This vegan dish is healthy and quick: a perfect emergency meal.

fields.name: Cauliflower Fried Rice
fields.ingredients: Cauliflower rice, eggs, garlic, ginger, soy sauce
fields.description: This meal can easily be made vegan by substituting beans for eggs without sacrificing any of the flavor

fields.name: Jello
fields.description: Home-made jello is cheaper and healthier than store-bought!

fields.name: Pesto Sandwich
fields.description: Frying or grilling chicken in a thick pesto sauce makes for a warm, tasty meal.

fields.name: Lo mein
fields.ingredients: Lo mein, beef, shallot, peas, soy sauce
fields.description: This staple dish is remarkably versatile and allows for any kind of vegetable to be substituted.

fields.name: Chicken Satay
fields.description: This protein-heavy meal only serves as an entree -- make sure to have a side dish!
